== Series 2 (2014)==

Toast of London will return for another 6-part series in 2014. On the 13th of May 2014, co-author Arthur Matthews talked of a plot for an episode in the Radio Times: "We discover that he [Stephen Toast] is Britain's second best actor acting in high wind. The leading British actor, who's really great (not Brian Blessed as you might think, he must have been too obvious), gets blown away and Toast steps into the breach."<ref>http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-05-13/toast-of-london-series-2-teasers-acting-in-high-winds-and-more-clem-fandango</ref> Also, in one episode, "Match Fit", Toast tries to beat his rival Ray Purchase in the 'Celebrities and Prostitutes Blow football tournament'<ref>http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-09-30/toast-of-london-series-2---first-look-spoiler-free-review</ref>. The series is set to debut on November 3rd. <ref>http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a606161/josh-homme-in-toast-of-london-exclusive-first-picture-of-qotsa-frontman.html#~oU6ZmNwEKaPMoK</ref>

